      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SO GLAMOROUS (4) turned spotting a big start finishing fifth (22.73) last time in a Grade 5 at Shepparton. Should be very hard to beat this time. DUKE CABOOM (3) drew a squeeze box and was game in defeat when a close second, a head from the winner Tornado Tahlia (22.39) at this track. The form out of his last race has been franked. Hard to beat again. SOLAR JESSIE (7) turned in a moderate run last time when seventh at this track over 390m behind Ultimo (22.70) in a Grade 5. Was in the money prior to that. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings four times from eight attempts. Can do much better this time. IT'S SOYSAGES (5) can run a bold race on best form.",
